    <h2 id="whatissm">Ideation</h2>
    <div>
      <h3>PROPERLY SCOPING WHAT A POSTAL WORKER CAN AND CANNOT DO</h3>
      <p>
        It is important to note that initial proposals of Carriers that Care
        were met with a lot of hesitation from user testers. Having conducted
        user interviews with seven individuals with ages ranging from 20s to
        50s, centering our questions around allowed us to sort concerns into
        four categories:
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
      <img
        style="border-style: none;"
        src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dbiwj2oo8/image/upload/v1709585139/Group_47_etzxgi.svg"
      />
      <div class="grid-twocol">
        <div></div>
      <p>
        Across all seven interviewees, the tangible aspects of Carriers That
        Care was universally agreed with to be valuable. However, there was
        concern over the concept of relying on letter carriers to report on
        senior wellbeing - the idea of 'caring for seniors' is accompanied by
        nuanced implications of medical care and invasion of privacy, which
        would put seniors in a vulnerable position as letter carriers would be
        granted a position of authority without going through the proper
        training.
<br>
        Given our results, there was a need to properly define the domains in
        which a letter carrier would support within Carrier that Care. In order
        to accomplish this, we evaluated a framework by the NIA that defines
        four essential pillars that are crucial to supporting ageing comfortably
        at home.
      </p>
    </div>
      <div>
        <img
          style="border-style: none;"
          src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dbiwj2oo8/image/upload/v1709584835/Frame_299_roqfla.svg"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="grid-twocol">
        <div></div>
      <p>
        Amongst the four pillars, we scoped our service and moved forwards with
        an focus on designing around improving social connections to reduce
        loneliness and social isolation, a domain that postal workers can
        reasonably intervene with without reducing the credibility or trust in
        Carriers That Care.
      </p>
    </div>
    </div>
